## Section 1: Prerequisites & Verification Script

Run this script in PowerShell to verify your environment is ready:

```powershell
# Check PowerShell version
$version = $PSVersionTable.PSVersion
Write-Host "PowerShell Version: $version"

if ($version.Major -lt 6) {
    Write-Host "❌ PowerShell 6+ required. You have version $version" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "Install PowerShell 7: winget install Microsoft.PowerShell" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "Or download from: https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/releases" -ForegroundColor Yellow
} else {
    Write-Host "✅ PowerShell version OK" -ForegroundColor Green
}

# Check if winget is available
if (Get-Command winget -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) {
    Write-Host "✅ winget available" -ForegroundColor Green
} else {
    Write-Host "❌ winget not found" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "Install from Microsoft Store: App Installer" -ForegroundColor Yellow
}

# Check if Copilot CLI is installed
if (Get-Command copilot -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue) {
    $copilotVersion = copilot --version
    Write-Host "✅ Copilot CLI installed: $copilotVersion" -ForegroundColor Green
} else {
    Write-Host "⚠️ Copilot CLI not installed" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "Install with: winget install GitHub.Copilot" -ForegroundColor Yellow
}
```

### Prerequisites Checklist

- [ ] PowerShell 7+ installed
- [ ] winget available
- [ ] GitHub Copilot subscription active
- [ ] Copilot CLI installed
- [ ] Workshop repository cloned